body:
@arunmahadevan 
Could you submit a pull request which documents this feature to asf-site?
After submitting pull request I'll merge this.

Secondly, I don't necessarily like the idea of `ResourceIsolationInterface` taking up responsibility for starting and stopping workers.. This would be moving a lot of responsibility from supervisor to `ResourceIsolationInterface` specially when we do a lot of setting-up/tearing-down for worker and use worker-launcher in multitenant cases. I would have simple interface which may help us call from within supervisor - and possibly more than once..- without any side-effects so that we may call them again in case of partial failures.

```
public interface ResourceAllocationInterface {
boolean reserveResourcesForWorker(workerid, resources);
boolean releaseResourcesForWorker(workerid);
```
